3 ways to include css
 1. Inline CSS
 2. Internal or embedded CSS
 3. External CSS file


Example

div.span{
         background-color:blue;
         color:white;
}




INLINE CSS

   <p style= "color:green;">It is example of inline styling</p>

INLINE CSS IS USED IN THE SINGLE LINE FOR THE ELEMENT 




INTERNAL CSS

<head>
  <style>
      p{
        color:red;
        }
   </style>
</head> 

INTERNAL CSS IS USED FOR THE ENTIRE ELEMENT WHEN PARTICULARY CALLED 


EXTERNAL CSS

<head>
    <link ref= "stylesheet" href = "style.css">
<head>



NOTE:
Inline CSS will be taken as top preference if all the type or ways of CSS is used 



4 Ways of selecting the CSS

 1. CSS element selectors 
 2. CSS ID selectors
 3. CSS class selectors
 4. The CSS grouping selectors



